WEBVTT

00:08.660 --> 00:12.360
Great news.
I just got us tickets
to The Bodyguard.

00:12.403 --> 00:16.103
Mom, I know you're a little
pop-culture challenged,

00:16.146 --> 00:18.105
but that's not in theaters
anymore.

00:20.237 --> 00:23.762
No, not the movie,
the musical.
At the Pantages.

00:23.806 --> 00:25.634
That's nice of you,
but why?

00:27.592 --> 00:30.073
We don't do enough things
together as a family.

00:30.117 --> 00:33.250
I begged you to let me
choreograph something
for all of us.

00:33.294 --> 00:34.860
Look, I thought
seeing The Bodyguard

00:34.904 --> 00:36.384
would be a fun thing
to do together,

00:36.427 --> 00:37.689
just the four of us.Good call.

00:37.733 --> 00:39.604
I love The Bodyguard.

00:40.692 --> 00:42.085
Just the five of us.

00:51.442 --> 00:53.836
Will everyone
please stop yelling?
I mean...

00:53.879 --> 00:55.229
I'm sorry.

00:55.272 --> 00:57.318
My open mic
went pretty late last night,

00:57.361 --> 00:58.667
so I didn't get
much sleep.

00:58.710 --> 01:00.451
I killed, by the way.

01:00.495 --> 01:01.757
Oh, that's right.

01:01.800 --> 01:04.107
Getting back in the comedy
game, huh, Dad?

01:04.151 --> 01:07.197
Yeah, well, I mean,
don't call it a comeback.
I've been here for years.

01:10.679 --> 01:13.421
Wait.
Aren't Clark and Connor
having a thing tomorrow?

01:13.464 --> 01:16.772
Yeah, but it's casual.
I'm sure we can miss it.

01:16.815 --> 01:18.861
It's definitely not something
we need to drag the kids to.

01:18.904 --> 01:20.863
Oh, please.
Clark and Connor
would understand.

01:20.906 --> 01:22.647
It's The Bodyguard.

01:30.090 --> 01:31.874
Hey, everybody, listen.
Quick reminder,

01:31.917 --> 01:33.136
our barbecue
is this weekend,

01:33.180 --> 01:34.616
so Connor and I
need to get a head count.

01:34.659 --> 01:36.835
No big deal,
should be super chill.

01:36.879 --> 01:38.228
You know what, Clark,
we're not gonna make it.

01:38.272 --> 01:39.490
Pat's taking me
out of town.

01:39.534 --> 01:40.970
No! No, you can't.

01:41.013 --> 01:42.319
Ah, sorry to miss it,

01:42.363 --> 01:45.017
but the lovely isle
of Santa Catalina calls.

01:46.062 --> 01:47.759
Can't you go
another weekend?

01:47.803 --> 01:49.109
Afraid not.

01:49.152 --> 01:51.546
No, this is mating season
for their world-famous bison.

01:51.589 --> 01:55.071
And the hotel's room deposit
is non-refundable,

01:55.115 --> 01:57.160
and I'm almost
comedically cheap.

01:58.988 --> 02:00.294
Okay, please,
please, please,

02:00.337 --> 02:01.773
tell me you guys
are gonna be there.

02:01.817 --> 02:03.514
Um, quick question,

02:03.558 --> 02:05.777
will this be
a vegan barbecue?

02:05.821 --> 02:08.345
Obviously. Violence begins
with the fork. Why?

02:10.260 --> 02:11.392
No reason.

02:13.089 --> 02:14.917
I see you.
I see him do...

02:14.960 --> 02:16.919
We actually do
have plans.

02:16.962 --> 02:19.313
We're all gonna see
The Bodyguard
at the Pantages.

02:19.356 --> 02:21.053
[SCOFFS]
Can't you go see that
some other weekend?

02:21.097 --> 02:22.577
We already bought tickets,

02:22.620 --> 02:24.709
and the kids and D.K.
are going, so...

02:24.753 --> 02:26.537
Well, our barbecue
is family-friendly,

02:26.581 --> 02:28.844
so D.K. and the kids
are more than welcome.

02:28.887 --> 02:30.237
I guess I can see
if there's some way

02:30.280 --> 02:31.760
to dump off the tickets,
but I...

02:31.803 --> 02:33.240
Great, you're in.
This is a verbal contract.

02:33.283 --> 02:34.458
I will see you tomorrow.

02:34.502 --> 02:36.156
I said I would try.Fine!

02:41.944 --> 02:43.163
Listen, sweetie,

02:43.206 --> 02:45.600
I am just as freaked out
as you are,

02:45.643 --> 02:48.385
but Pat and Damona
are going to Catalina.

02:48.429 --> 02:51.736
Yes, Connor,
they know about the bison.

02:51.780 --> 02:54.086
Well, yeah,
because no one knows
it's our surprise wedding.

02:54.130 --> 02:56.350
KEN: Oh, my God.

02:58.917 --> 03:00.223
I have to go.

03:02.660 --> 03:04.009
Ken.

03:04.053 --> 03:05.359
Nope.

03:06.142 --> 03:08.536
How much did you hear?

03:08.579 --> 03:10.755
And why do you sleep
with your head covered?

03:10.799 --> 03:12.931
I didn't hear anything.

03:12.975 --> 03:14.324
And my nose gets cold.

03:16.065 --> 03:18.241
You guys are actually
doing it?

03:18.285 --> 03:19.677
We're doing it.

03:19.721 --> 03:21.244
[SQUEALING, LAUGHTER]

03:21.288 --> 03:23.507
I am so happy for you.Yeah, thanks,

03:23.551 --> 03:26.206
except it's gonna be
this total disaster.Oh, no.

03:26.249 --> 03:28.599
You'll hear that a lot,
but marriage has its moments.

03:28.643 --> 03:30.166
No.

03:30.210 --> 03:32.386
The wedding,
no one's even
gonna show up.

03:32.429 --> 03:34.170
Well,
maybe if you told people.

03:34.214 --> 03:36.085
No. no, no, no.
It has to be a surprise.

03:36.128 --> 03:38.522
When Connor and I went to
our friends' surprise wedding,

03:38.566 --> 03:40.307
it was just,
it was so lovely
and amazing

03:40.350 --> 03:41.960
to watch the joy
on their guests' faces

03:42.004 --> 03:43.571
when they realized
what was happening.

03:43.614 --> 03:46.226
We just, we decided
that's how we wanted
to get married.

03:46.269 --> 03:49.794
That sounds
beautiful, but...Yeah.

03:49.838 --> 03:53.798
But you understand
you won't be getting
any gifts, right?

03:53.842 --> 03:56.366
Oh, no, am I on the hook
for a gift now that I know?No.

03:56.410 --> 03:57.672
We don't care about gifts.

03:57.715 --> 03:59.717
We just want our friends
to be there.

03:59.761 --> 04:01.806
[LAUGHING] Then why'd you
call it a vegan barbecue?

04:01.850 --> 04:03.721
[LAUGHS MOCKINGLY]

04:03.765 --> 04:05.419
Oh, hey.

04:05.462 --> 04:06.637
Now that you know,
maybe, maybe,

04:06.681 --> 04:08.335
do you think that you could
convince people to come?

04:08.378 --> 04:10.250
You got it, buddy.
Consider it done.

04:10.293 --> 04:12.077
But you can't tell anyone,
not even Allison.

04:12.121 --> 04:14.341
Please, we barely even talk
anymore.

04:20.869 --> 04:23.045
Oh, hey, guys.

04:23.088 --> 04:26.788
So I think I'm gonna drop in
on Clark's thing after all.
[CHUCKLES]

04:26.831 --> 04:28.398
Oh, hey,
maybe you should, too.

04:28.442 --> 04:30.574
No, we told you
we're gonna be in Catalina.

04:30.618 --> 04:32.924
Yeah.
Just an hour ago,
you weren't going either.

04:32.968 --> 04:35.144
Well, yeah,
that's the exhaustion
talking.

04:35.187 --> 04:37.364
I mean, it's hard to come
down from such an epic set.
[CHUCKLES]

04:39.104 --> 04:40.758
But, you know,
Clark's a friend,

04:40.802 --> 04:43.065
and, you know,
we should be there for him.

04:43.108 --> 04:44.719
You know, to be there.

04:44.762 --> 04:47.635
For him.

04:47.678 --> 04:51.682
Yeah, it's just this hotel's
cancellation policy
is really strict,

04:51.726 --> 04:53.118
especially when you book
the honeymoon suite.

04:53.162 --> 04:54.511
[GASPS] Pat!

04:54.555 --> 04:56.644
Ah, that was meant
to be a surprise.

04:56.687 --> 04:59.124
Oh! Pat,
that is so nice.

04:59.168 --> 05:00.474
Well, it was
the only room available.

05:00.517 --> 05:02.476
Damn! I was gonna keep that
to myself.

05:04.173 --> 05:05.957
Okay, look, guys.

05:06.001 --> 05:08.830
Trust me,
you do not
want to miss this.

05:08.873 --> 05:11.528
I mean, not that
anything's gonna happen,
but if it did,

05:11.572 --> 05:13.095
you'd never
forgive yourselves.

05:20.581 --> 05:23.061
Are Clark and Connor
getting married?

05:23.105 --> 05:24.933
[SQUEALS]What?

05:24.976 --> 05:26.978
No! No, of course not!
No!

05:27.022 --> 05:29.633
You know what?
I overheard Clark

05:29.677 --> 05:32.244
talking to somebody about
officiating something.

05:32.288 --> 05:33.985
Well, that had
absolutely nothing to do

05:34.029 --> 05:35.160
with Clark and Connor.

05:35.204 --> 05:37.119
Oh.

05:37.162 --> 05:39.251
Okay, well,
if not them, then...

05:45.170 --> 05:47.390
Are you and Allison
renewing your vows?

05:49.349 --> 05:50.567
Yes.

05:50.611 --> 05:52.134
I knew it.

05:52.177 --> 05:53.091
I knew it. I knew it.

05:53.135 --> 05:54.310
I'm like 4% psychic.

05:54.354 --> 05:56.007
I knew it. I knew it.

05:56.051 --> 05:57.531
Oh, my God.

05:57.574 --> 05:58.749
Well, why are you being
so weird about it?

05:58.793 --> 06:00.142
Wait a minute.

06:00.185 --> 06:02.231
Are you secretly
not married?

06:02.274 --> 06:06.148
I mean, have you been
living in sin all these years?

06:06.191 --> 06:08.542
Oh, your poor
illegitimate children.

06:09.891 --> 06:11.371
No!

06:11.414 --> 06:13.938
Pat, we're just
renewing our vows.

06:15.375 --> 06:17.028
Why?
Because they expired
and went bad?

06:18.508 --> 06:20.162
I've been there.

06:20.205 --> 06:23.208
Look,
you can't tell Allison.
I'm surprising her.

06:23.252 --> 06:25.123
And you can't tell Clark
I told you.

06:25.167 --> 06:26.516
Well,
why would Clark care?

06:26.560 --> 06:27.952
You know, I mean,
Clark's really into

06:27.996 --> 06:29.519
this whole thing
being a surprise.

06:29.563 --> 06:31.086
You know, so keep
your big mouth shut,
you two.

06:31.129 --> 06:33.218
[LAUGHS][SQUEALS]

06:34.132 --> 06:35.569
Oh, my God![LAUGHS]

06:40.530 --> 06:42.706
Night, Damona.
See you Monday.

06:42.750 --> 06:44.969
You mean I'll see you tomorrow
at Clark's barbecue, right?

06:45.013 --> 06:47.058
Yeah, I thought about it,
and we're gonna skip it.

06:47.102 --> 06:49.713
We're all really excited
to see The Bodyguard.

06:49.757 --> 06:51.323
At least, D.K. is.

06:52.890 --> 06:55.502
Um, does Ken know
you're not going?

06:55.545 --> 06:56.938
We haven't talked about it
since this morning,

06:56.981 --> 06:58.069
but I don't think
he'll care.

06:58.113 --> 06:59.288
Okay, um...

07:00.289 --> 07:01.421
So, um, you,
you know,

07:01.464 --> 07:03.379
we had canceled our plans

07:03.423 --> 07:06.556
because it's really, really
important to be there.

07:06.600 --> 07:09.124
Oh,
that's nice of you.Mm-hmm.

07:09.167 --> 07:10.604
Anyway, have fun.Wait, wait!

07:10.647 --> 07:12.257
Wait, wait, listen.

07:12.301 --> 07:13.389
You got to be there.

07:13.433 --> 07:14.869
Okay.

07:16.261 --> 07:17.872
Don't tell Ken I told you,

07:17.915 --> 07:20.091
but he's planning
a vow renewal ceremony.

07:20.135 --> 07:22.572
He is? Oh, my God!

07:22.616 --> 07:24.356
Yes, and it's a surprise,

07:24.400 --> 07:26.054
so please don't tell Ken
I told you.

07:26.097 --> 07:27.969
No, I won't,
I won't say a word.

07:28.012 --> 07:29.710
Oh.

07:29.753 --> 07:31.886
You know, I...
I pretty much stopped

07:31.929 --> 07:34.018
expecting anything
romantic out of Ken.

07:35.933 --> 07:39.589
Especially the way
he mangled Valentine's Day.

07:39.633 --> 07:41.852
I figured we'd just live
out our golden years

07:41.896 --> 07:43.419
as good married friends.

07:45.116 --> 07:46.204
Boy, was I wrong.

07:46.857 --> 07:48.337
[SQUEALS]

07:55.387 --> 07:56.693
Hey, got a sec?

07:56.737 --> 07:58.565
Of course, sweetheart.

08:01.002 --> 08:02.264
Hey, you don't have
to be sarcastic.

08:04.484 --> 08:07.225
Look, I thought it over,
and I think
it's important for us

08:07.269 --> 08:08.662
to go to Clark's barbecue.

08:08.705 --> 08:10.707
I'm already
one step ahead of you.

08:10.751 --> 08:12.492
I already dumped
The Bodyguardtickets.

08:12.535 --> 08:15.538
[LAUGHING] Wow.
That was easy.

08:15.582 --> 08:18.280
Well, I sensed
it was important to you,

08:18.323 --> 08:21.022
and, as my husband
of 20 years,

08:21.065 --> 08:23.938
if it's important to you,
it's important to me.

08:23.981 --> 08:25.417
Hey, I just combed that.

08:27.202 --> 08:30.597
Oh, and I got the kids
and D.K. to go, too,

08:30.640 --> 08:32.773
so, you know,
we'll all be there.

08:33.382 --> 08:35.123
Huh. Papa, too.

08:36.037 --> 08:37.995
Mm, okay.

08:38.039 --> 08:40.563
Ken, I just love you
so much.

08:43.827 --> 08:44.959
Cool.

08:46.700 --> 08:50.268
Maybe later I can
show you how much.

08:50.312 --> 08:51.966
Eh, you're coming
to the barbecue.
That's good enough.

08:52.009 --> 08:53.576
[LAUGHS]

09:01.410 --> 09:03.455
Wow.
This place looks amazing.

09:03.499 --> 09:05.588
Your dad really
out-did himself.

09:06.328 --> 09:07.808
D.K.: It's okay.

09:07.851 --> 09:09.461
Not worth missing
The Bodyguard.

09:11.028 --> 09:13.814
Grandpa,
have you ever considered

09:13.857 --> 09:16.207
just seeing it
on another day?

09:16.251 --> 09:19.471
I don't need you
to solve this, Dave,
just be there for me.

09:19.994 --> 09:21.430
[GROANS]

09:21.473 --> 09:22.823
PAT: Ah.

09:22.866 --> 09:24.172
Hey.

09:24.215 --> 09:25.390
Hey, lovebirds.

09:25.434 --> 09:27.088
So glad you could make it.

09:28.785 --> 09:30.744
I had no idea
you were coming.

09:32.746 --> 09:35.749
So wonderful
to have you here.

09:35.792 --> 09:38.795
Yeah, I just, just wish
it wasn't so expensive.

09:38.839 --> 09:40.928
He's just mad because
the hotel's being funny
with our deposit.

09:40.971 --> 09:42.451
Yeah.

09:42.494 --> 09:43.713
[CELLPHONE VIBRATES]Oh. Mm.

09:43.757 --> 09:46.498
Well...
Ah, speak of the devils.

09:46.542 --> 09:48.979
I'll give them
a piece of my mind.

09:49.023 --> 09:51.503
Hello. No, you listen to me.
What?

09:51.547 --> 09:52.592
No, I'd be happy to hold.

09:54.811 --> 09:59.120
♪ The one that makes me
go all night long

09:59.163 --> 10:02.166
♪ The one that makes me
think of youOh, they even got music.

10:02.210 --> 10:04.342
Allison, check it out,
Blink-182!

10:04.386 --> 10:06.388
[CHUCKLES]I know.

10:06.431 --> 10:08.825
♪ That's all you gotta do Who?

10:08.869 --> 10:12.002
I don't know. I thought they
were the guys who play outside
the 7-Eleven on Moorpark.

10:13.395 --> 10:15.266
Hey, hi.
Oh, so pretty.

10:15.310 --> 10:16.616
Can we steal Ken
for just a second?

10:16.659 --> 10:18.661
Oh, yeah.

10:18.705 --> 10:20.445
Bring him back.
I need him.

10:22.447 --> 10:24.275
Okay, we have
a bit of an emergency.

10:24.319 --> 10:25.799
Our friend Shelly
was gonna officiate,

10:25.842 --> 10:27.627
but she can't make it.Yeah,
she's down with the flu,

10:27.670 --> 10:28.889
and now we don't know
what to do.

10:28.932 --> 10:30.804
Oh, I'd say liquids, rest...

10:30.847 --> 10:32.327
Ken!

10:32.370 --> 10:33.763
Sorry. I, um...

10:35.591 --> 10:37.201
I'll officiate.

10:37.245 --> 10:38.812
Oh, um, uh...

10:40.988 --> 10:42.772
[BABBLES]

10:42.816 --> 10:45.035
But you have to, like,
get ordained online.

10:45.079 --> 10:46.776
How long does it take?30 minutes.

10:46.820 --> 10:49.779
Give me
a laptop and a Coke Zero,
and I can do it in 28.

10:52.695 --> 10:55.916
All right.
Well, thanks anyway.

10:55.959 --> 10:57.352
Well, looks like

10:57.395 --> 10:58.962
we're gonna have to eat
that hotel deposit.

10:59.006 --> 11:01.008
Unh-unh.
I do not eat deposits.

11:02.270 --> 11:04.446
Hi. Hi, Tanya.

11:04.489 --> 11:06.100
You just talked to my
boyfriend, Pat Hein.

11:06.143 --> 11:07.362
[CHUCKLES]

11:08.232 --> 11:09.625
Uh-huh.

11:09.669 --> 11:11.279
No, I know, but,

11:11.322 --> 11:13.281
God, I would hate
to have to call the
L.A. Times

11:13.324 --> 11:16.153
and tell them about your
bedbugs and your shower rats.

11:17.328 --> 11:19.026
Uh-huh.

11:19.069 --> 11:20.114
Uh-huh.

11:20.157 --> 11:21.289
Okay.

11:23.508 --> 11:25.859
I just got us credit.
We can use it
anytime we want.

11:25.902 --> 11:28.209
Uh, I'm not so sure
I still want to go...

11:28.252 --> 11:30.385
I mean, what,
with the shower rats.

11:34.128 --> 11:35.172
Hi.

11:38.610 --> 11:40.569
I'm so glad you're here.

11:41.570 --> 11:43.615
I'm so glad I'm here, too.

11:45.879 --> 11:47.271
Wait.

11:47.315 --> 11:48.533
Do you know?

11:51.667 --> 11:53.364
I do. Are you mad?

11:53.408 --> 11:55.889
Oh, I could never be mad
on this day.

11:57.412 --> 11:59.719
This is so much better
than The Bodyguard.

11:59.762 --> 12:01.155
That's what I was
trying to tell you.

12:01.198 --> 12:02.939
[CHUCKLES]

12:02.983 --> 12:04.114
Thank you.

12:12.949 --> 12:14.908
Um, if I could have
everyone's attention.

12:25.832 --> 12:27.050
We've got
a little surprise.

12:27.094 --> 12:28.269
Is it meat?

12:33.013 --> 12:35.102
Better.

12:35.145 --> 12:39.193
The real reason
we're here today
is because...

12:39.236 --> 12:41.935
Clark and Connor
are getting married.

12:41.978 --> 12:44.241
[ALL GASP, CHEER]

12:44.285 --> 12:45.939
So everyone fill your glasses.

12:45.982 --> 12:47.418
We're gonna start
in about five minutes.

12:47.462 --> 12:49.899
[INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS]

12:49.943 --> 12:53.207
Oh, my God.
Allison, I feel horrible.

12:53.250 --> 12:55.600
Ken must have said
you were renewing your vows
just to get us here.

12:55.644 --> 12:57.385
No, no, no. It's fine.

12:57.428 --> 13:00.431
I'm just happy
for Clark and Connor.

13:00.475 --> 13:02.303
Are you sure?
You're good?

13:02.346 --> 13:03.347
[LAUGHING] Yeah.

13:03.391 --> 13:04.871
Yeah. Yeah.

13:05.480 --> 13:06.742
Yeah...

13:07.351 --> 13:08.918
Yeah.

13:08.962 --> 13:11.616
Okay, 'cause you just said
"yeah" a whole lot of times.

13:11.660 --> 13:13.053
[SIGHS] Yeah.

13:17.884 --> 13:19.581
♪ Me, babe

13:19.624 --> 13:22.976
♪ Marry me

13:25.282 --> 13:29.460
♪ If I ever get the nerve
to say hello in this cafe

13:29.504 --> 13:32.202
♪ Say you will

13:32.246 --> 13:33.682
♪ Mm-hmm

13:34.509 --> 13:37.381
♪ Say you will

13:37.425 --> 13:38.556
♪ Mm-hmm

13:39.688 --> 13:41.864
♪ Marry me

13:42.473 --> 13:45.041
♪ Mm-hmm

13:46.651 --> 13:48.523
[CHEERS AND APPLAUSE]

13:53.920 --> 13:55.356
Blink-182, everybody.

13:57.662 --> 13:59.447
He's from Train.

13:59.490 --> 14:01.275
And he's one of
Connor's best friends.

14:01.318 --> 14:03.190
Read the program.

14:08.282 --> 14:09.544
As a married man,

14:09.587 --> 14:11.459
I look back and remember
how daunting

14:11.502 --> 14:14.505
the prospect
of finding a spouse was.

14:14.549 --> 14:17.204
Was there really such
a thing as a soul mate?

14:17.247 --> 14:19.989
I mean, for me,
that question was answered

14:20.033 --> 14:22.470
the moment I first met
my wife, Allison.

14:22.513 --> 14:24.472
You know,
it's more than love.

14:24.515 --> 14:26.126
Allison fills me up

14:26.169 --> 14:29.390
and is the missing piece
to my puzzle.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.958
She confirmed
that soul mates were real

14:32.741 --> 14:34.438
and that she was mine.

14:34.482 --> 14:36.919
And it's clear to everybody

14:36.963 --> 14:39.574
that Clark and Connor
are soul mates.

14:41.706 --> 14:43.752
